(8) Other justifications, like in the case of request for write-off due to loss of documents, the circumstances of the loss should be stated in the letter of request; and
•	To include the Loan Receivables-Others (General Fund) amounting to ₱293,800 on the Status Report of Receivables - Other Receivables, reflecting the complete details such as account number, the purpose, date granted, due date of liquidation, age, status of accountable officer, employee, or recipient, availability of documents, and action taken (demand letters issued).

We recommended Management to initiate the creation of additional mandatory LDRRMO staff for administration and training, research and planning, and operations and warning through any or a combination of the following options as provided under RA 10121, and NDRRMC, DILG, DBM, and CSC Joint MC No. 2014-1:

•	Designation or assignment of personnel of LGU to the LDRRMO in concurrent capacities with their existing positions;
•	Reassignment of personnel of the LGU to the LDRRMO;
•	Full-time or part-time detail of existing personnel of other government agencies to the LDRRMO; and/or
•	Transfer of existing vacant position from other units to the LDRRMO. Accordingly, such vacant positions shall be abolished and positions appropriate to the LDRRMO shall be created.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

Prepare the Aging Schedule of Accounts Payable, showing all the names of the creditors and other information and retrieve all the supporting documents to support the validity of the recorded accounts payable of P2,790,981.05;
Provide adequate disclosure about these accounts payables in the Notes to Financial Statements to provide users relevant information of the account; 
Revert to the Unappropriated Surplus (Government Equity) the   Accounts Payable which are already two years or more outstanding, in which no administrative or judicial claim has been filed, or those that have no valid supporting contracts/documents; and,
Adjust the retirement gratuity erroneously lodged under AP

We recommended that management:
Instruct the Municipal/Project Engineer to conduct and ocular inspection of the project and in coordination with the Contractor, require the updated Statement of Work Accomplished and Time Elapsed to establish the correct status of the project; 
Direct the Municipal Engineer to evaluate properly, the validity of the cause of delay due to unfavorable weather condition was beyond the ordinary unfavorable weather condition requirement and in excess of the time already considered in the determination of the original contract time during the conduct of detailed engineering and in the preparation of the contract documents as agreed upon by the parties before contract perfection as required in item 11, Annex E of the Revised IRR of RA No. 9184, to justify the time extension granted which fall within the critical  of the PERT/CPM; and impose liquidated damages, if warranted, as a result of the delayed completion of the project in consonance with the Revised IRR of RA 9184 and the contract agreement between the LGU of Naawan and Jejor’s Construction Corporation before final payment is made in the project;
Enjoin the BAC Chair and the Municipal Engineer to submit immediately the additional required contract documents of the project, together with complete bidding documents and thereafter, instruct them to submit all perfected contracts   within five days from the execution of a pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001 dated February 12, 2009; and
Instruct the Municipal Engineer to monitor completion of construction of the Municipal Building in accordance with the agreed timeline.

We recommended Management to submit the following for review and evaluation in compliance to CSC Memorandum Circular No. 1, s. 2001:
Copy of the LGU Program on Awards and Incentives for Service Excellence (PRAISE) or the Employee Suggestions and Incentive Awards System duly approved by the Civil Service Commission for CY 2021. Such copy of the annual report on the awards and incentives system which should be submitted to; the CSC on or before the 30th day of January;
Agency annual work and financial plan and budget showing that at least 5% of the HRD Funds was allocated for the PRAISE;
Proof showing that the monetary awards shall be granted only when the suggestions, inventions, superior accomplishments and other personal efforts result in monetary savings which shall not exceed 20% of the savings generated; and
Justification/explanation on the procedures in evaluating the nominees and the mechanism for recognizing the awardees.

