We recommended to Management the following remedial measures:

Direct the inventory committee to conduct an immediate physical count of all its property, plant and equipment. This committee may be composed of the heads or representatives from the Office of the Municipal Treasurer, the Municipal Accountant, the Municipal Engineer, and a representative from the Office of the Municipal Mayor. They are required to submit the RPCPPE on or before January 13 of each year, copy furnished the COA Auditor concerned pursuant to Section 124 of NGAS Manual for LGUs, Volume I;

Require each Department Head to conduct every year a physical inventory count of all properties under their office and to submit inventory report to the inventory committee for the random validation of the existence of the property;
Further, the committee should be required to check the condition of the property. Any damage, obsolete and unserviceable property shall be reported in the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) and Waste Materials Report and immediately request for disposal. Lastly, the inventory reports should be reconciled with the accounting records to determine the correctness of the property records;

Additional personnel to assist both the Accountant and Treasurer to prepare and maintain records and ledgers all properties owned by the Municipality; and

Provide depreciation to all its depreciable assets and adjust the Government Equity for the unaccounted accumulated depreciation of the previous years in order to fairly present the accounts in compliance to Paragraph 27 of PPSAS No. 1.

